               <msContents>
                  <summary>Biblical Readings for the Horologium, Book of Hours, ሰዓታት: ዘአቡነ: ጊዮርጊስ: </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1"><locus from="1r" to="27r" facs="003"/><title>Lectionary Readings for the Nighttime Prayers</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gə‘əz</textLang>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1"><title>Opening Benediction:</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gə‘əz</textLang>
                  <note><foreign xml:lang="gez">በስመ፡ አብ፡ <gap reason="omitted"/> ባርከነ፡ እግዚኦ፡ በበረከተ፡ ነቢያት፡ ቅዱሳን፡ በአቡነ፡ አዳም፡ በአቤል፡ በሴት፡ በሄኖክ፡ በቃይንናን፡ በመላልኤል፡ በያሬድ፡ በማቱሳላ፡ በላሜህ፡ በኖኅ፡ በሴም በያፌት፡ ወበመልከ፡ ጼዴቅ፡ <gap reason="omitted"/></foreign></note>
                </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2"><locus from="3r" to="27r" facs="005"/><title>Readings for the Seven Days of the Week</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gə‘əz</textLang>
                  <note><title type="complete" ref="LIT3575Mashaf"/> adopts the pattern set forth in the Liturgy, but introduces an innovation for the readings for Saturday. Thus, Sunday through Friday have the regular readings: 1) Reading from the Pauline Epistles; 2) Reading from the General Epistles; 3) Reading from the <title type="complete" ref="LIT1019Actsof"/>; 4) Reading from the Introductory hymn from the <title type="complete" ref="LIT2000Mazmur"/>, the so-called <foreign xml:lang="gez">ምስባክ፡</foreign>; and 5) Reading from the Gospels. But, on Saturday the pattern is: 1) Reading from <title type="complete" ref="LIT1793Leviti"/>; 2) Reading from <title type="complete" ref="LIT1685Bookof"/>; 3) Reading from the <title type="complete" ref="LIT1019Actsof"/>; 4) Reading from the Introductory hymn from the <title type="complete" ref="LIT2000Mazmur"/>, the so-called <foreign xml:lang="gez">ምስባክ፡</foreign>; and 5) Reading from the Gospels</note>
                  </msItem>
                </msItem>
